Symbol: RASGRP1 Name: RAS guanyl releasing protein 1 Synonyms: CalDAG-GEFII, RASGRP HGNC_ID: 9878 EntrezGene_ID: 10125 RefSeq_ID: NM_005739 SemanticZoomLevelVisibility: 4 TransparencyZoomLevelVisibility: 0
RasGRP1 specifically activates H-Ras in the Golgi. It is localised in the cytosol in quiescent cells. After PMA stimulus, at first it moves to the PM and then shifts towards other subcellular compartments, like the Golgi apparatus. PMID:12782630 RasGRP1 is a C1-domain containing protein that is activated by DAG and Ca2+, in a manner analogous to members of the PKC family. RASGRP1 activates Ras through the exchange of bound GDP for GTP. PMID:17496910 Activation of PKC: http://users.rcn.com/jkimball.ma.ultranet/BiologyPages/S/Second_messengers.html RecName: Full=RAS guanyl-releasing protein 1; AltName: Full=Calcium and DAG-regulated guanine nucleotide exchange factor II; Short=CalDAG-GEFII; AltName: Full=Ras guanyl-releasing protein;

Identifiers_begin: HUGO:HRAS1 Identifiers_end References_begin: RasGDP binds to Sos and RasGTP is generated. RasGTP keeps Sos inactive enhancing duration and amplitude of the output. PMID:17496910 RasGRP1 activates Golgi-associated Ras on this compartment. PMID:16488589 K-Ras is found exclusively at the PM. H- and N-Ras are also present in endomembrane compartments such as the endoplasmic reticulum and the Golgi apparatus. PMID:12782630 Processed K-Ras is confined primarily to the PM; however, when its polybasic region is phosphorylated o r targeted by Ca2+/calmodulin, K-Ras relocalises to other endomembrane compartments, including Golgi, endoplasmic reticulum and mitochondria. In contrast, H-Ras and N-Ras constantly shuttle between the Golgi and PM as a result of a constitutive depalmitoylation/repalmitoylation cycle. Ras phosphorylates Raf1. PMID:17496910 H-Ras but not K-Ras signalling was dependent on endocytosis. PMID:19615955 Modelling choices: - for the moment, all the three isoforms (H-, N-, K-) are represented by this component References_end
